defaultQ79 default&#xa0; 
defaultBob Blackman:default Fine. What checks have you undertaken to ensure that people applying for registration have not been excluded by another scheme?
defaultEmma Clancy:default This is a new condition of authorisation brought in by DCLG, and it is effective from June. Scheme operators are obliged to share that information, and indeed there is a system in place to ensure that we do that. So it is something that has happened in the past on a fairly informal basis, and it is one of the things that have been improved. As I have said, it comes into effect from June. That process is in place, so we will share and check. We ask at the moment, but the process will be further tightened by the new procedures.
